cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new efficient nonlinear one-class classifier for outlier detection. The method operates in a reproducing kernel Hilbert subspace and uses the kernel trick for nonlinear mapping of the data. These characteristics suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
